cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper is about video super-resolution, which is a computer vision task, hence it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) category. The proposed method uses deep learning techniques, which suggests it could also belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) category. The paper also involves the use of a neural network to predict offsets, which could fall under the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of adaptive alignment, which could fall under the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. Finally, the paper involves the use of a reconstruction network, which could fall under the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) category.
